Sheep pox and goat pox, Russia
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 15 Oct 2015 from Dr Evgeny Nepoklonov, Deputy Head, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance, Ministry of Agriculture, Moscow, Russia.

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 24 Sep 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 12 Oct 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 13 Jan 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Capripoxvirus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Kamyshovoe, Khasansky, Primorskiy Kray [Primorye]
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Sep 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 18 / 18 / 0 / - / -
Affected population: private subsidiary farm

Outbreak 2: Kraskino, Khasansky, Primorskiy Kray [Primorye]
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Sep 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
